[[File:Cave bug icon.png|left]]
'''Cave bugs''' are monsters that require level 7 [[Slayer]] to kill. They are found in the [[Lumbridge Swamp Dungeon|Lumbridge Swamp Caves]], requiring a [[light source]] and a [[rope]] to enter, and stronger variants can be located in the [[Dorgesh-Kaan South Dungeon]]. They are a good source of low level herbs, which can aid beginning players in training [[Herblore]]. Their [[Hitpoints]] regenerate about 20 times faster than normal.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1441718443565191174|date=25 September 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.is/uULWi|archivedate=25 September 2021|quote=They have about 20x faster than normal regeneration.}}

Cave bugs that are significantly more powerful—with a combat level of 96—can be found in the Dorgesh-Kaan South Dungeon, located south of the city of [[Dorgesh-Kaan]], but can only be accessed after the completion of the [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]] quest through fairy ring {{fairycode|AJQ}}.

A [[light source]] is required for these dungeons, along with a rope to place down on the hole leading to the Lumbridge Swamp Caves, if it has not been done so previously.

Players should be on the lookout for [[wall beast]]s within the Lumbridge Swamp Caves, which are monsters that will grab and attack you, if you are in their line of sight. To avoid being hit, either stand one square directly beside a hole in the wall and run across to the other side, or have a [[spiny helmet]] equipped.

